The paper deals with a computer vision task of detecting visual relations in images, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of fully convolutional networks and deep learning techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of RoI pooling, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as subject-predicate-object relations, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
